  "body": "### Description\r\nModify how V3 database works to prepare for new V4 database (to be added in #2181).  When transactions are committed to storage, three transactions will be required:\r\n\r\n1. Commit new data to the hot database\r\n2. Commit newly finalised data to the finalised database\r\n3. Commit deletion of finalised data from the hot database\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Backwards compatible with existing databases\r\n* Data is not lost when finalised data fails to write\r\n* Moving data to finalised \"catches up\" automatically if previous moves failed. ie the failed data is moved along with the next batch of finalised data.\r\n\r\nPart of #1965, designed to get things setup for #2181\r\n",
